    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-18T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-18T12:00:00-05:00" n="778"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d778">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Conference files, lot 60 D 627, <gloss
                        target="#t_CF1">CF</gloss> 320: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-18T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 18, 1954—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 197. Eyes only Secretary from Under
                    Secretary. Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_DCD1">Dillon</persName> has
                    telephoned suggesting that on my return I touch down Paris and see <persName
                        corresp="#p_MFP1">Mendes-France</persName> at airport on condition that he
                    is invested, which <persName corresp="#p_DCD1">Dillon</persName> expects today
                    or tomorrow.<note n="1" xml:id="d778fn1">Memoranda from <persName
                            corresp="#p_JUA1">Johnson</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_SWB1"
                            >Smith</persName>, June 18 and 19, concerning Ambassador <persName
                            corresp="#p_DCD1">Dillon</persName>’s call and a possible meeting
                        between Under Secretary <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">Smith</persName> and
                        Premier <persName corresp="#p_MFP1">Mendès-France</persName> are in
                        Conference files, lot 60 D 627, <gloss target="#t_CF1">CF</gloss>
                        320.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_DCD1">Dillon</persName> says that <persName
                        corresp="#p_MFP1">Mendes-France</persName> urgently desires to see me.
                    Because of French reaction to <persName corresp="#p_CSWLS1">Churchill</persName>
                        visit<note n="2" xml:id="d778fn2">For documentation on Prime Minister
                            <persName corresp="#p_CSWLS1">Churchill</persName>’s visit to
                        Washington, June 25–29, see <ref target="frus1952-54v06p1">volume <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">vi</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> and for other reasons, I will do this, unless I hear from you
                    to contrary.<note n="3" xml:id="d778fn3">The Department’s reply was contained in
                        telegram <gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 218, June 18, <ref
                            target="#d779">
                            <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> Plan to leave here Sunday afternoon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
